title: GVCC Dryer Road Mountain Bike Race

description: Event will be held on a 12.5 mile 4 right hand turn road course. notes:

directions: Race start and finish is at 3537 State Hwy. 51 in New Lisbon, NY   13415.   Race start and finish is roughly 4 miles North of Morris, NY on Route 51. Or, 4 miles South of Garrattsville, NY.

title: Nancy Morgenstern Memorial 2010 Fall Bear Mountain
web_page: www.crca.net - note that this is a placeholder, I need to build the actual CRCA page for this race
description:
ATTENTION CANADIAN and other riders with  FOREIGN  LICENSES
Enter INTL for your license.

The Nancy Morgenstern Cup
The winner of the Women\'s 1/2/3 race will receive the Nancy Morgenstern Cup and have their name engraved with all previous winners on the cup.

All race winners will receive a special Nancy Morgensterm Memorial jersey.

Staging - Start and Finish 
The staging area and registration is at Lake Sebago  with the start at Lake Sebago and the finish on the top of the hill after the turn from Sebago on to Lake Welch Drive. The 14 mile loop is the same as in past races but with a different start and finish.

Register early. Entry Fees increase by $5 on August 30.

Course Map - 
Note that the W is the feed zone and the + near the 1 mile mark is the FINISH LINE

click to see map and elevation profile

Race manual html or pdf

Start Times
The 9:00 races and Pro/1/2 at 10:15 will start at specified time. The starting time of other races is approximate depending on pace of other races. They will not start before specified time. 
 
Wait Lists
Riders on wait lists will be moved into the race fields in order of sign up as we receive cancelations. On race day, riders remaining on the wait list checkin at registration. They will be given numbers after registration closes for an event and we get the list of no-shows. Numbers are given out in order of sign up on bikereg. If there are not enough spots, refunds will be given. In the past everyone on the wait list got to race.

 
Wheels support
SRAM neutral field support will be provided for the Men\'s Pro/1/2 and other races depending on the availability of cars.  Other fields will be provided wheels in-wheels out support.

Race Rules
All riders should familiarize themselves with the race manual, found on the event web page. The yellow line rule will be strictly enforced. Blocking of the opposing traffic lane during the race is a serious violation of our agreement  with the Parks Commission. Please keep the entrance road to the parking lot and the perimeter road in the parking lot clear.

Licenses
A valid USCF or UCI license is required for all riders. Cat 5 men and Cat 4 women may purchase a 1-day license for $10. As per USCF rules, riders are responsible for registering for the correct category. Rdiers registering for wrong category are subject to disqualification and suspension.
course:
Staging - Start and Finish 
The staging area and registration is at Lake Sebago  with the start at Lake Sebago and the finish on the top of the hill after the turn from Sebago on to Lake Welch Drive. The 14 mile loop is the same as in past races but with a different start and finish.
directions: Palisades Interstate Parkway to exit 16. Follow Lake Welch Parkway to entrance to parking area. The Palisades Parkway can be accessed from the south via the New York State Thruway I-87/287 (Exit 13N), by the north via Bear Mountain Bridge, or by the west from route 6 (Exit 16 from I-87)

title: Buck Hill Cyclocross
course: This is a great cyclocross course. We have a good section of paved road (slight uphill), followed by a good section of gravel driveway (flat). A short section that goes through the woods is generally full width and flat with only a few little bumpy spots and some twists and turns. After the woods, you\'re back in open farm field, heading down the smooth, grassy access road. It\'s mostly down hill to the finish, but there are a few little twists. Most of the loopy/curvy stuff is in the start/finish area where you\'ll loop back and forth, dismount a couple times and sprint in front of the barn and all your screaming, cow-bell ringing fans. There are three spots you\'ll get off the bike (most people will) - one triple barrier, and two natural obstacles of the short steep hill nature.
notes: Open Men and Women, Juniors, Masters Men and Women
directions: 59 Buck Hill Road SOUTH, Mecklenburg, NY

title: MassenaCross
description: A cyclocross race hosted at the Massena Town Beach
course: A 2.95km course on dirt, grass, sand, and brief sections of pavement.  Course includes a sand pit, steep climb, natural barriers, and one man made barrier.
registration: Registration on bikereg.com.  Registration closes Sept 24th, 2010 at noon.
notes: USCF rules apply.  No aero-bars, no bar-ends.  Mountain bikes (without bar-ends) are allowed.  Pit area will be available.  CPSC approved helmet required.
directions:
From Canada: ake the 401 to Cornwall (US Bridge/Brookdale Avenue Exit) and follow Brookdale Ave/CR-2 East/Provincial Route 138 S. Enter roundabout and take exit to continue following Provincial Route 138 S/Seaway International Bridge. After processing at U.S. Customs, follow the roundabout to the second exit onto NYS 37 W. Follow NYS 37 W into Massena. Turn right on rt 420 (Main St) and follow till it comes to a T.  Turn Left at the T on Rt 131.  Beach will be a few miles down on the right.  Massena is less than 20 minutes from Cornwall.

From Syracuse: take US 81 N to Alexandria Bay, exit 50N, to NY 12 N which will become NYS 37 E. Stay on NYS 37 E to Massena. Turn left on NYS 420 (Main St) and follow till it comes to a T.  Turn Left at the T on Rt 131.  Beach will be a few miles down on the right.

From NYC/Albany: take US 87 N (Adirondack Northway) to Plattsburgh; bear right onto exit ramp 42 (Mooers/Rouses Point) to US 11. Turn left onto US 11 and follow US 11 to Malone. Turn right onto NYS 37 W in Malone and continue on NYS 37 W into Massena. Turn right on NYS 420 (Main St) and follow till it comes to a T.  Turn Left at the T on Rt 131.  Beach will be a few miles down on the right.
